(I) EACH AUTHORIZATION FOR PET CREMATION SIGNED BY
THE PET OWNER OR PET OWNER’S AGENT;
(II) EACH IDENTIFICATION RECORD, INCLUDING TAGS, LABELS,
OR TRACKING DOCUMENTATION USED TO IDENTIFY PET CREMAINS; AND
(III) A LOGBOOK FOR EACH PET CREMATION COMPLETED THAT
SPECIFIES:
1. THE DATE OF CREMATION;
2. THE METHOD OF CREMATION; AND
3. THE NAME OF THE INDIVIDUAL WHO PERFORMED THE
CREMATION.
(3) EACH LICENSEE SHALL ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN REASONABLE
PROCEDURES TO ENSURE THE CONFIDENTIALITY AND SECURITY OF ALL RECORDS,
INCLUDING PERSONALLY IDENTIFYING INFORMATION RELATED TO A PET OWNER
OR CREMATED PET.
7–4B–06.
– 14 –

WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 547
(A) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SUBTITLE IS GUILTY OF A
