(2) THE ATTORNEY GENERAL MAY SUE FOR AND A COURT MAY
GRANT:
(I) INJUNCTIVE OR OTHER EQUITABLE RELIEF;
(II) IMPOSITION OF A CIVIL PENALTY NOT EXCEEDING $5,000;
OR
(III) BOTH.
7–4B–07.
THIS SUBTITLE AND TITLE 5, SUBTITLE 7A OF THE BUSINESS REGULATION
ARTICLE MAY BE CITED AS THE MARYLAND PET CREMATION CONSUMER
PROTECTION ACT.
